---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { OPPORTUNITIES } from '../../data/calendar.ts';
// The traveller's view: the fairs and biennials worth planning a trip around, so you do not
// miss the one happening where you are headed. The calendar and the itinerary, one machine.
const travel = OPPORTUNITIES
  .filter((o) => o.kind === 'fair' || o.kind === 'biennial')
  .sort((a, b) => (a.city < b.city ? -1 : 1));
---
<Base path="/itineraries" title="Art Itineraries" description="The fairs and biennials worth a trip, worldwide, so you never miss the one where you are headed. Art travel for the culturally-curious, built around the calendar.">
  <section class="wrap" style="padding-block: clamp(2rem,6vw,4rem) 1rem;">
    <p class="eyebrow">Department</p>
    <h1>Art Itineraries</h1>
    <p class="lede prose">You travel, and you would rather not miss the fair everyone will be talking
      about. Here is what is worth planning a trip around, by city, so the dates reach you before
      the flights fill. The calendar tells you when. Itineraries tell you how to go.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap" style="padding-block: 1rem;">
    <h2>What is worth the trip</h2>
    <ul class="ops">
      {travel.map((o) => (
        <li class="op"><a href={`/opportunity/${o.id}`}>
          <span class="eyebrow">{o.kind === 'fair' ? 'Fair' : 'Biennial'}</span>
          <span class="op-title">{o.title}</span>
          <span class="muted">{o.city}, {o.country}</span>
          <span class="muted">{o.verified && o.deadline ? `Dates around ${o.deadline}` : o.window}</span>
        </a></li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  </section>

  <style>
    .ops { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 1rem 0 0; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; }
    .op { border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 3px; background: var(--paper); }
    .op a { display: grid; gap: 0.25rem; padding: 1rem; text-decoration: none; }
    .op-title { font-family: var(--serif); font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.15rem; }
  </style>
  <section class="wrap" style="padding-block: 1rem 3rem;">
    <h2>Built around the calendar</h2>
    <p class="muted prose">An itinerary starts from a real date on the Global Art Calendar, a fair
      in Cape Town or a biennial in Sharjah, and builds the trip around it: what to see, who to
      meet, where the art actually is. The diaspora traveller flying in for the fair is a reader
      we plan for by name.</p>
    <p class="muted prose">The travel and lifestyle partners pay. The reader gets the guide, and a
      real benefit when one is on offer. Itineraries are in development; the first routes follow
      the calendar’s strongest dates.</p>
    <p style="margin-top:1.5rem;"><a class="btn ghost" href="/">See the calendar</a></p>
  </section>
</Base>
